headline: Morgan Stanley's PE arm to sell HVAC firm to Goldman Sachs Alternatives
summary: Pennsylvania-based Sila will be sold to the private equity unit of Goldman Sachs Alternatives, Morgan Stanley said on Monday, but did not disclose the financial terms of the deal.  Reuters had reported in September that a transaction could value Sila, which provides residential HVAC, plumbing and electrical services, at about $1.5 billion, including debt.  HVAC companies have emerged as a lucrative target for private equity firms due to their stable cash flows and the essential nature of services they provide.

headline: Morgan Stanley Capital Partners Agrees to Sell Sila Services
summary: NEW YORK, November 11, 2024--Investment funds managed by Morgan Stanley Capital Partners ("MSCP") today announced they have entered an agreement for the sale of Sila Services ("Sila" or the "Company") to the Private Equity business at Goldman Sachs Alternatives ("Goldman Sachs"). As part of the transaction, Sila management will continue to lead the Company and retain a significant minority stake. Financial details of the transaction were not disclosed.

headline: Dive Deposits: Morgan Stanley can’t keep everyone
summary: The bank may have developed a reputation for persuading executives to stay. But its co-head of investment management just left to become CEO of an asset management unit at  insurance giant Prudential.
